169 to 173-177 (only part of hich is shown) Henry Street, vest of, adjoining, and at the N.. corner of Jefferson Street, showing the Beth Abraham Chasidim D'S'lonim Synagogue (No. 169). The congregation was organised in 1897 and conducts its services in Hebrew and Yiddish. Shown on the left is a portion of the Rabbi Jacob Joseph School, No. 165-167,   June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
